1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,720
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:04,820
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:09,880
My name is Catherine and today we have an intermediate level lesson all about a very
我是Catherine，今天我们有一个中级课程，内容是关于一种非常

4
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:14,480
special kind of person who helps you out with your kids.
特殊的人，他们能帮你照顾孩子。

5
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:15,480
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,480
Today we want to get a nanny.
今天我们想找一个保姆。

7
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,480
A nanny.
一个保姆。

8
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:18,480
A nanny.
一个保姆。

9
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:23,760
So, a nanny is a person, usually a woman, but it can be a man as well I guess.
所以，保姆就是一个人，通常是女性，但我想也可能是男性。

10
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:26,880
And this person takes care of your children when you're working or when you're out
这个人会在你工作或外出时照顾你的孩子。

11
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:27,880
of the house.
外出时。

12
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:28,880
That's right.
没错。

13
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:30,080
So, this is what's going on today.
所以，这就是今天的内容。

14
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:34,600
We're going to see what type of responsibilities a nanny has.
我们来看看保姆有哪些职责。

15
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:37,880
And so, let's listen to her dialogue and we'll be back in a bit.
那么，让我们听听她的对话，一会儿再回来。

16
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:45,760
Hey Mel, are you up for some tennis today?
嘿，Mel，今天想打网球吗？

17
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,280
Sorry, I can't.
抱歉，我去不了。

18
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:52,200
I have to go to work, pick up Jake and Maddie from school, and make them an afternoon snack,
我得去上班，然后接Jake和Maddie放学，给他们做下午点心，

19
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:55,760
then take Jake to soccer practice and Maddie to dance class.
再带Jake去足球训练，Maddie去舞蹈课。

20
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,760
You sound exhausted.
你听起来累坏了。

21
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:00,240
Maybe you should hire a nanny to help you out.
也许你应该雇个保姆来帮忙。

22
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:04,360
She can pick the kids up and take them to their after school activities.
她可以接孩子放学，带他们去参加课外活动。

23
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:07,560
She can also help you do some household chores and run some errands.
她还可以帮你做些家务和跑腿。

24
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:09,680
Oh, I don't know.
哦，我不知道。

25
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,560
It's hard to find the right nanny.
很难找到合适的保姆。

26
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:15,940
You have to consider her previous work experience, the responsibilities you give her, and how
你得考虑她以前的工作经验、你给她的职责，以及她

27
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:17,640
she interacts with the kids.
和孩子们的互动情况。

28
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,720
I would love to have someone to help me out though.
不过，我确实希望有人能帮我。

29
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:22,280
I think you should definitely consider it.
我觉得你绝对应该考虑一下。

30
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:26,280
This way you won't have to juggle such a busy schedule and you'll still get to spend
这样你就不用忙得团团转，还能在晚上

31
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:28,680
time with the kids in the evenings.
和孩子们在一起。

32
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:31,840
I can refer you to this great nanny, Amy.
我可以给你推荐一个很棒的保姆，Amy。

33
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:35,000
She used to work for my neighbors before they moved away.
她以前在我邻居家工作，直到他们搬走。

34
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,640
She's very responsible, a good cook, and great with kids.
她非常负责，厨艺好，而且很会带孩子。

35
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,600
Oh, that's great.
哦，那太好了。

36
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,600
Thanks Grace.
谢谢Grace。

37
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,600
Can you give me her number?
你能给我她的电话号码吗？

38
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,920
I'll talk it over with Julie and give her a call tomorrow.
我会和Julie商量一下，明天给她打电话。

39
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:48,440
Maybe this way I won't be so tired every day and Julie and I might even get to go on a
也许这样我就不会每天那么累了，Julie和我甚至还能偶尔

40
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:51,400
date once in a while.
约个会。

41
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:54,400
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

42
00:01:54,400 --> 00:02:00,120
So now let's take a look at some key words on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们看看“语言要点”中的一些关键词。

43
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,640
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

44
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:06,880
So as you said, Marco, we don't just find a nanny, we hire a nanny.
所以，正如你所说，Marco，我们不只是找一个保姆，而是雇一个保姆。

45
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,760
So what does the word hire mean?
那么，“hire”这个词是什么意思？

46
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:14,640
Okay, so we have the verb to hire someone and that means to get someone to work for
好的，我们有动词“hire someone”，意思是让别人为你工作，

47
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:18,200
you and you pay them obviously money in exchange for their services.
你付给他们钱作为服务的交换。

48
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:22,560
Okay, so this is different from finding a job for someone because I could find a job
好的，这和帮别人找工作不同，因为我可以帮别人找工作，

49
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:25,760
for someone but maybe that job is at a restaurant.
但那份工作可能是在餐馆。

50
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:31,000
But when I hire someone, that means I want that person to work for me or for my company.
但当我“hire”某人时，意味着我想要那个人为我或我的公司工作。

51
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,000
That's right.
没错。

52
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:37,280
So in this case, obviously we are not a company, we are just a couple of people who are looking
所以在这种情况下，显然我们不是公司，我们只是几个在找

53
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,560
for a nanny.
保姆的人。

54
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,040
So we need to hire a nanny.
所以我们需要雇一个保姆。

55
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:44,080
We need to get her to work for us and obviously you would pay her a salary.
我们需要让她为我们工作，显然你会付给她薪水。

56
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:47,920
Alright so when you pay her a salary, you also have some expectations about what the
好的，当你付薪水时，你也会对保姆的职责有一些期望。

57
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,440
nanny will do.
会做什么。

58
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:54,160
So one of those expectations is that the nanny will take the children to their after school
其中一个期望就是保姆会带孩子去参加他们的课外

59
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,160
activities.
活动。

60
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,160
That's right.
没错。

61
00:02:56,160 --> 00:03:01,960
So this is a phrase if you will or a type of thing that happens after school.
所以这是一个短语，或者说是一种放学后发生的事情。

62
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:07,000
So usually children, when they finish their classes, they have some things that they can
通常孩子们上完课后，他们可以在学校做一些事情，

63
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
do at school like for example sports.
比如运动。

64
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
That's right.
没错。

65
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,560
So this is very common in America but not so common in other parts of the world.
所以这在美洲很常见，但在世界其他地方不那么常见。

66
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:20,440
So just to explain, if your child is in high school or middle school, after school is over,
解释一下，如果你的孩子在高中或初中，放学后，

67
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:25,280
there's no more class, your child might want to play soccer or to go to art class.
没有课了，你的孩子可能想踢足球或去上美术课。

68
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:30,720
And these are things that you do at the school but it's usually considered an activity, not
这些是在学校做的事情，但通常被认为是活动，而不是

69
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,720
a class.
课程。

70
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,680
So we call these after school activities.
所以我们称之为课外活动。

71
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,680
That's right.
没错。

72
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:38,400
So these activities are usually for recreation.
所以这些活动通常是娱乐性质的。

73
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,960
They're not really part of the curriculum.
它们不是课程的一部分。

74
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,480
It's not a class.
不是课程。

75
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,600
No, you don't get marks or grades for these.
不，这些活动没有分数或成绩。

76
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,920
These are just for fun.
只是为了好玩。

77
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:51,400
A lot of people work and so they need to have these activities for their kids to stay at
很多人要工作，所以他们需要让孩子参加这些活动，以便孩子在学校

78
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,160
school until they finish working.
待到他们下班。

79
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,160
That's right.
没错。

80
00:03:54,160 --> 00:04:00,160
Okay, so we want the nanny to take the children or pick them up from their after school activities
好的，所以我们希望保姆带孩子或接他们从课外活动回来。

81
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:05,280
and we also need the nanny to help out with some household chores.
而且我们还需要保姆帮忙做一些家务。

82
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,560
Okay, so you should know where these chores are being done.
好的，所以你应该知道这些家务是在哪里做的。

83
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,880
The first word is household which means in the house.
第一个词是 household，意思是“家里的”。

84
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:18,840
Okay, so examples of household chores would be like cleaning the windows.
好的，所以家务的例子包括擦窗户。

85
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,200
Washing the dishes.
洗碗。

86
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,880
Or doing laundry.
或者洗衣服。

87
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:26,000
So basically any type of cleaning around the house.
所以基本上就是家里各种清洁工作。

88
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,600
That's right, making the house look nicer.
没错，让房子看起来更漂亮。

89
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,600
And so usually children have chores.
通常孩子们会有家务活。

90
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:35,080
These are things they need to do but a nanny can also help with household chores.
这些是他们需要做的事情，但保姆也可以帮忙做家务。

91
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:39,560
Okay, and also we want the nanny to help and run some errands.
好的，而且我们还希望保姆帮忙跑一些腿。

92
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,200
Okay, so this is funny.
好的，这挺有趣的。

93
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:48,640
This phrasal, this phrase uses the word to run but we're not running like a sport.
这个短语用了“run”这个词，但我们不是像运动那样跑步。

94
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:52,440
We're going to do some errands but the verb here is to run errands.
我们要去办些差事，但这里的动词是“run errands”。

95
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,240
So Marco, on Sunday I have to run some errands.
所以 Marco，星期天我得去办些差事。

96
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,720
I'm sorry I can't go out to the movie with you guys.
抱歉，我不能和你们一起去看电影了。

97
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:00,880
Okay, so to run errands, what does that mean?
好的，那么“run errands”是什么意思？

98
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:06,000
Well an errand is like a job or a task that you have to do but it's usually not something
嗯，差事就像是你必须做的工作或任务，但通常不是

99
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,760
you get paid for.
有报酬的。

100
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:13,240
To run an errand is like to go to the grocery store and pick up food or to pick up your
跑腿就像去杂货店买食物，或者去洗衣店取

101
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,240
clothes at the laundromat.
衣服。

102
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,200
You have dry cleaning.
你有干洗的衣服。

103
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:21,800
Okay so they're kind of like chores I guess but you don't really do them in the house.
好的，所以它们有点像家务，但我想你并不是在家里做。

104
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,120
You have to go outside and run these errands.
你得出去跑这些腿。

105
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:26,480
You have to go pay your bills for example.
比如你得去付账单。

106
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:30,520
Exactly and so when I was growing up, on the weekends my mother would always run all of
没错，我小时候，周末我妈妈总是去办她所有的

107
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,400
her errands because during the week she had to work.
差事，因为工作日她得上班。

108
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,440
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

109
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,200
So a lot of interesting words there.
所以那里有很多有趣的词。

110
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:40,560
I think we can go ahead and listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit
我想我们可以继续听一遍对话，稍后回来

111
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,280
with Fluency Builder.
进行流利度训练。

112
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:50,760
Hey Mel, are you up for some tennis today?
嘿 Mel，今天想打网球吗？

113
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,280
Sorry, I can't.
抱歉，不行。

114
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:57,080
I have to go to work, pick up Jake and Maddie from school and make them an afternoon snack
我得去上班，接 Jake 和 Maddie 放学，给他们做下午点心，

115
00:05:57,080 --> 00:06:00,920
then take Jake to soccer practice and Maddie to dance class.
然后带 Jake 去足球训练，带 Maddie 去舞蹈课。

116
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,920
You sound exhausted.
你听起来累坏了。

117
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,400
Maybe you should hire a nanny to help you out.
也许你应该雇个保姆来帮你。

118
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:09,520
She can pick the kids up and take them to their after school activities.
她可以接孩子，带他们去课外活动。

119
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:12,760
She can also help you do some household chores and run some errands.
她还可以帮你做些家务和跑腿。

120
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,840
Oh, I don't know.
哦，我不知道。

121
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:16,720
It's hard to find the right nanny.
很难找到合适的保姆。

122
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:21,100
You have to consider her previous work experience, the responsibilities you give her and how
你得考虑她以前的工作经验、你给她的职责，以及她

123
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,800
she interacts with the kids.
和孩子们的互动。

124
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,880
I would love to have someone to help me out though.
不过我很想有人帮我。

125
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,440
I think you should definitely consider it.
我觉得你绝对应该考虑一下。

126
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:31,680
This way you won't have to juggle such a busy schedule and you'll still get to spend time
这样你就不用应付这么忙的日程，而且晚上还能

127
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,800
with the kids in the evenings.
和孩子们在一起。

128
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:37,000
I can refer you to this great nanny, Amy.
我可以推荐一个很棒的保姆给你，Amy。

129
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,120
She used to work for my neighbors before they moved away.
她以前在我邻居家工作，直到他们搬走。

130
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:43,920
She's very responsible, a good cook and great with kids.
她很负责，厨艺好，而且很会带孩子。

131
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,760
Oh, that's great.
哦，那太好了。

132
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,760
Thanks Grace.
谢谢 Grace。

133
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,760
Can you give me her number?
你能给我她的电话号码吗？

134
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:50,080
I'll talk it over with Julie and give her a call tomorrow.
我会和 Julie 商量一下，明天给她打电话。

135
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:53,600
Maybe this way I won't be so tired every day and Julie and I might even get to go on a
也许这样我就不会每天那么累了，Julie 和我甚至还能偶尔

136
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:59,320
date once in a while.
去约个会。

137
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:02,960
Alright we're back with Fluency Builder and so let's take a look at some of these phrases
好了，我们回到流利度训练，现在来看看这些短语。

138
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,120
now.


139
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,640
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

140
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:11,680
So this first phrase is a very spoken English phrase, something that you're going to hear
所以第一个短语是一个非常口语化的英语短语，你会经常听到，

141
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:15,320
all the time, especially if you're talking to your American friends.
尤其是和你的美国朋友聊天时。

142
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:18,360
We say, are you up for some tennis today?
我们说，“are you up for some tennis today?”

143
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,760
To be up for.
“To be up for”。

144
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,320
Okay, so to be up for something.
好的，所以“to be up for something”。

145
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:27,000
This is from the very first sentence when Grace says, hey Mel, are you up for some tennis
这来自第一句话，Grace 说，“嘿 Mel，今天想打网球吗？”

146
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,100
today?


147
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:31,540
What does it mean if I ask someone if they are up for some tennis?
如果我问某人是否“up for some tennis”，这是什么意思？

148
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,820
This means, would you like to play tennis today?
这意味着，“你今天想打网球吗？”

149
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:36,260
Are you interested in playing tennis today?
“你对今天打网球感兴趣吗？”

150
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:37,680
So is this a good idea for you?
所以这对你来说是个好主意吗？

151
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,960
Do you want to do this?
你想做这个吗？

152
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,560
So basically, are you willing to play tennis today?
所以基本上就是，“你今天愿意打网球吗？”

153
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,560
Yes.
是的。

154
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:46,080
Alright, so to be up for is to be interested in or willing to do something.
好的，所以“to be up for”意思是“对某事感兴趣或愿意做某事”。

155
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:48,320
Are you up for a movie tonight?
你今晚想看场电影吗？

156
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:54,400
Okay, or maybe you can ask your friend, are you up for grabbing a bite to eat later on?
好的，或者你可以问你的朋友，“你一会儿想出去吃点东西吗？”

157
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:55,400
Absolutely, I'm hungry.
当然，我饿了。

158
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,660
So to be up for is a good way to ask a question.
所以“to be up for”是提问的好方式。

159
00:07:58,660 --> 00:08:00,520
After that though, we have another phrase.
之后，我们还有另一个短语。

160
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,320
This phrase is very important when you're trying to get someone to help you.
这个短语在你试图找人帮忙时非常重要。

161
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,360
So how do we ask, can you help me?
那么，我们该怎么问“你能帮我吗？”

162
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:09,520
In the dialogue we saw how Mel said that it would be a great idea to get a nanny because
在对话中，我们看到梅尔说请个保姆是个好主意，因为

163
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:13,480
