她很想有人能帮我一把。

164
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:17,140
So to help someone out, to help me out.
所以“帮某人一把”，就是“帮我一把”。

165
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:21,000
So this is interesting because you could say, I need someone to help me.
这很有意思，因为你可以说“我需要有人帮我”。

166
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,680
But it's more common to hear the phrase, to help me out.
但更常见的说法是“帮我一把”。

167
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,880
So you're not going out.
所以并不是“出去”的意思。

168
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:29,000
It doesn't have to do with space.
这和空间无关。

169
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,160
But we just say this phrase, to help out, means to help someone.
但我们只说这个短语“帮一把”，意思是帮助某人。

170
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:36,160
So it's basically the exact same thing, but it just sounds a lot more natural.
所以基本上是一回事，但听起来自然得多。

171
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,160
Exactly.
没错。

172
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:39,160
So, Marco, I'm moving tomorrow.
那么，马可，我明天要搬家。

173
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,000
Do you have some time to help me out?
你有时间帮我一把吗？

174
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:45,720
Okay, so you say help me out, but you could also say, do you have time to help me?
好的，你说“帮我一把”，但也可以说“你有时间帮我吗？”

175
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,140
And both are okay.
两种说法都可以。

176
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:50,840
Or if I'm talking about me and my friend, we're really busy tomorrow.
或者如果我说我和我的朋友，我们明天真的很忙。

177
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,640
Do you have any time to help us out?
你有时间帮我们一把吗？

178
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,860
Okay, so we just changed the person there.
好的，我们只是换了人称。

179
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:56,360
We went to the plural form.
我们用了复数形式。

180
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,080
Me, us, you.
我、我们、你。

181
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,280
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

182
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:06,320
And so for our last phrase, this is actually also very interesting.
那么对于最后一个短语，这其实也很有意思。

183
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:12,280
When Grace was telling Mel that she's really busy and if she gets a nanny, she wouldn't
当格蕾丝告诉梅尔她真的很忙，如果她请个保姆，她就不必

184
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:14,600
